added.title: Free Perk
added.description: Robin teaches the Titans all about health insurance.

added.title: Go!
added.description: Robin struggles to lead the Titans after finding out that his catchphrase "GO!" is trademarked by another team.

added.title: Teen Titans Roar!
added.description: The Titans are outraged when their favorite cartoon is rebooted so they come up with a plan to get this new show off the air.

added.title: Tower Renovation
added.description: Following the destruction of their Tower by Slade, the Titans go house hunting.

added.title: Booty Eggs
added.description: Not wanting to be creeped out on Easter the Titans dispatch the Easter Bunny and take matters into their own hands.

added.title: The Slide
added.description: A chance encounter with the woman of his dreams inspires Rocky to stop living life online and find love with the help of the latest dating app. Gumball and Darwin try to help Rocky through the tricky world of online romance. In the race to find Rocky's dream girl, they discover people can forgive almost anything when you tell them you're acting in the name of love.

added.title: The Stars
added.description: When Dad gives Larry's hairdresser a bad review for saying he's bald, he gets offered a free haircut. This inspires Gumball and Darwin to go on a reviewing spree across town, forcing Larry to give them stuff with the threat of a bad review. Just because the customer is always right doesn't mean that what they're doing isn't wrong.

added.title: The Menu
added.description: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell them what it's called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

added.title: The Weirdo
added.description: When they see the school bullies making fun of Sussie, Gumball and Darwin decide to try and help her act less weird. They carefully observe her behavior and decide that the only thing they have to change is absolutely everything.

added.title: The Petals
added.description: When Leslie's petals begin falling off he feels like his good looks are fading, Gumball and Darwin use everything they know about style and beauty to try and help him. The only problem is they know nothing about style or beauty. As Gumball and Darwin's methods become more extreme, Leslie questions whether he's prepared to make the ultimate sacrifice for beauty.

added.title: Bears in the Dark
added.description: The Bears search for their missing box in a dark and scary cave.

added.title: Big Trouble Little Babies
added.description: When they realize they're too small for the rides at an amusement park, the Bears use a magic potion to get bigger.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: Mooshy Mon Mons
added.description: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Beth and the Beanstalk
added.description: After having a chocolate bar confiscated by Chef, Beth finds herself in a parallel giant world and aims to get back her now giant chocolate bar.

added.title: Pinata Regatta
added.description: Izzy can't bring herself to smash a Pinata during the class' Cinco De Mayo celebrations. But when that unsmashed Pinata comes to life and spawns an evil Pinata Army, it's batter up.

added.title: A Dame-gerous Game
added.description: After Leshawna, Bridgette, Owen and Cody win a Hide & Seek competition, they're trapped on a private island by a jealous former champion and forced to play for their freedom.

added.title: Pokin and Proddin
added.description: Valentino wins a coveted internship to work in the Tez administration. Initially intending to use his insider status to spy on Tez, Val unexpectedly finds himself enjoying the comradery of office life.

added.title: Stolen Retriever
added.description: When Vic cooks up a scheme to "borrow" people's dogs and return them for reward money, he gets in over his head with disastrous results!

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Keep It Fresh
added.description: It's Apple's turn to buy this months' groceries again meaning that the risk of starvation is at hand.

added.title: Panamanian Night Monkey
added.description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

added.title: Broccoli
added.description: Some major construction is taking place on the roof of Apple and Onion's building and they can't get back home till it's finished.

added.title: Cousin's Day
added.description: It's Cousin's Day- another holiday the corporations made up to make more money and Apple and Onion are going to capitalise on it.

added.title: Za
added.description: Pizza's Diner needs a makeover. Apple and Onion better get this right or Pizza is ruined.

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 1
added.description: With new Omni-Enhancements in tow, Ben looks to save a town from a sudden mudslide, but his heroics are short lived once Vilgax appears to warn our hero about the consequences of the Omnitrix's mysterious new alien.

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 2
added.description: After discovering that Vilgax has joined forces with the Weatherheads to trick him into turning over the Omnitrix, Ben must not only overcome his doubts, but fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat his foes.

added.title: Half-Sies
added.description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Xingo's Back
added.description: Left to entertain himself as Max takes a much deserved nap, Ben stumbles upon a Xingo arcade game and goes OE-Shock Rock to power it up, but when it receives too much juice, Xingo leaps out into the real world and our hero must go toe-to-toe with his favorite cartoon character.

added.title: Bounty Ball
added.description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

added.title: #ShockItToMe
added.description: Leslie Willis, the meanest girl in school, becomes a social media sensation by posting mean-spirited videos on her MetropoVids channel, causing Wonder Woman to question the moral integrity of the people who live in the World of Man.

added.title: #SheMightBeGiant
added.description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

added.title: #FightAtTheMuseum
added.description: Supergirl always relies on her strength, but she'll need more than brawn to stop brainy Catwoman from stealing valuable gems from the local science museum.

added.title: #FromBatToWorse
added.description: Having just moved to the boring Metropolis suburbs, Batgirl is thrilled when she intercepts a call from Batman asking for help. But before she can stop a visiting Gotham villain, she'll have to sneak past her dad, Police Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: #CrushingIt
added.description: Diana Prince is absolutely crushing it in every single aspect of life as a student at Metropolis High, until someone shows up who threatens to throw her off her game for good.

added.title: Idiosyncratic Induction
added.description: On Elliott's first day at the Hive, he meets the most unusual characters on his adventure so far.

added.title: Memory Mayhem
added.description: Frankie tries to discover more about the mysterious rock that bought them to their new home, with the help of an entity called The Head.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: Too Short to Ride
added.description: Steven and Amethyst take a trip to Funland but run into trouble when their friend is too short to ride the rollercoasters.

added.title: The New Lars
added.description: Steven gets a new look into Lars' life.

added.title: Beach City Drift
added.description: Steven and Connie get into a high-speed car race with their biggest foe.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Stray Bullet
added.description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
added.description: Him brings the Rowdyruff Boys back, protecting them from the girls' feminine wiles.

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet "n" Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Secret Swapper of Doom
added.description: When the girls get a Paper Fortune Teller that can predict the future if they tell it a secret, they begin to rely on it to predict everything. But when it predicts the Powerpuff Girls will be destroyed, the girls must find a way to stop the future from happening.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: The Squashening
added.description: To escape a monster, the girls have to tell him a scary story.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks
added.description: Upon returning to Ooo, Finn and Jake discover that there have been some radical changes in their absence.

added.title: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
added.description: Ice King weaves a tale filled with drama, romance, and men's fashion.

added.title: Elements Part 3: Winter Light
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Ice King travel to the new Ice Kingdom to confront the person responsible for turning everything topsy-turvy.

added.title: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
added.description: Before they can restore Ooo, Finn and Jake will have to escape exile in an endless sky.

added.title: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
added.description: Finn and Jake infiltrate the new Slime Kingdom and are drawn into a heated skate battle.

added.title: Claudus
added.description: Lion-O's dad King Claudus arrives on Third Earth, and turns out to be a big selfish jerk! Now Lion-O has to deal with his dad before he goes to war with the rest of the Thundercats.

added.title: Telethon
added.description: In order to save the Berbils, Cheetara uses her psychic powers to project a telethon into the brains of everyone on Third Earth.

added.title: Mall-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra builds a mall that's actually a giant labyrinth designed to trap the Thundercats forever. Too bad the Thundercats love the mall so much they could literally spend all eternity there.

added.title: Eclipsorr
added.description: Third Earth's sun is being blocked out by the Eclipsor Corporation, an amoral company that wants to sell its energy for a profit. The ThunderCats can't do anything about it because they don't have a spaceship, yet!

added.title: Wizz-Ra
added.description: The ThunderCats freak out when a spooky ghost dressed like a pharaoh appears in their mirrors! They quickly set about to getting rid of every reflective surface in their lair, because that ghost is scary and no one wants to talk to him!

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: The Explorer's Club
added.description: The ninja must break into the Explorer's Club to obtain the second Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu, running afoul of the club's manager and irate club-members.

added.title: Vengeance Is Mine!
added.description: Aspheera arrives at the Monastery of Spinjitzu and confronts Wu, forcing one of the ninja to make a heroic sacrifice.

added.title: A Cold Goodbye
added.description: Having learned Zane is not dead, Master Wu prepares to go after him, but Lloyd and the other ninja take matters into their own hands and defy their Master.

added.title: Clarence Loves Shoopy
added.description: When Clarence discovers that one of his neighbors is the grumpy school recess proctor Ms. Shoop - he gets a glimpse of her home life and decides the only things she's missing are some friends. Clarence sets out on a mission to match the cranky oddball Shoop with some new pals!

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Chad and the Marathon
added.description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

added.title: Officer Moody
added.description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

added.title: Gilben's Different
added.description: Gilben's newly sprouted peach fuzz sparks a discussion about puberty that ultimately convinces Clarence to act more like an adult.

added.title: Skips in the Saddle
added.description: Skips wants to start dating again.

added.title: Thomas Fights Back
added.description: Thomas Wants to get the park founder's statue back.

added.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
added.description: Skips must plan the perfect bachelor party for his cousin, Quips.

added.title: Tent Trouble
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby must replace CJ's expensive tent before she realizes they destroyed it.

added.title: Real Date
added.description: Mordecai and CJ want to go on a romantic date.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Claiming he's good at heart, Dynamo convinces Axel and the team to help him find a battery that can power his centrifuge and free him from Madtrap's control - but Bobbie Blobby isn't buying the baddie's story.

added.title: The Thing in the Wall
added.description: When Axel and the team accuse Galileo of stealing their possessions, the lizard must hunt down the true culprit - a mysterious creature behind the wall - to prove his innocence.

added.title: Madtrap
added.description: Madcap and Princess SugarSalt trap Axel and the team inside a Minergy-powered labyrinth that attacks them with their greatest fears, forcing them to work together and escape as a unit.

added.title: To Tame the Perilous Skies!
added.description: With Axel's drone-wing broken, the team must find another way to stop Madcap and his minions as they take to the skies in toy airplanes for an aerial assault on the city park.

added.title: Four Color Fallout
added.description: Axel, Galileo, and Sarge get Minergy-transported by Madcap into the pages of Axel's favorite comic book, the hero of which turns out not to be so cool after all.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Brawl Bot
added.description: Dr. Fox is proud to unveil her new ultimate combat machine and take it into an underground scientist fighting ring. But Hawkodile's jealous of Dr. Fox's fighting bot that's supposedly a better puncher than him and declares he can beat anything it can. To prove his point, he dresses up in spare robot parts and enters himself secretly in the bot battle. With Unikitty as his fighting coach, can Hawkodile survive the tourney, prove he's tougher than a machine, and avoid the scrap yard?

added.title: Beach Daze
added.description: Unikitty and the gang gear up for a fun day at the beach... but when Master Frown shows up as the lifeguard to spoil their plans in the sand, Unikitty and the gang embark on a beach quest to find the legendary Perfect Spot, far away from Frown's tyrannical rule. But can they get there before Frown and claim it for their own or will their quest turn out to be a real beach bummer?

added.title: Big Pup, Little Problem
added.description: After a mishap in the lab, everyone in the castle- except for Puppycorn- is shrunk to tiny size! Puppycorn thinks it's cool. His friends are like living action figures! So he begins playing with them in imaginary adventures. Unikitty and the others think being miniature and playing with Puppycorn is surprisingly fun, but PC has a habit of accidentally breaking his toys, and it's soon clear the gang will have to make a daring, tiny escape back to the lab before Puppycorn loves them to pieces!

added.title: Tragic Magic
added.description: After Richard puts on an amateur magic show, Dr. Fox becomes obsessed with figuring out how his science-defying tricks are done. But as she sets about using all of her genius intellect finding experimental ways to pull off the little pup's party tricks, will she accidentally ruin the wonder of magic?

added.title: Dancer Danger
added.description: Unikingdom's throwing a kingdom-wide dance, a fun event where everyone dresses up and busts a move. Everyone's excited... except for Richard, who's terrified to let loose and feel his inner groove. Unikitty knows Rick needs to express himself but can she and the others convince him to break out of his shell with some minor robotic body enhancements?

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Lord Cowboy Darrell
added.description: Everyone is forced to deal with some major changes at Boxmore.

added.title: Hope This Flies
added.description: Rad attempts to upgrade his van and make it fly.

added.title: The Perfect Meal
added.description: KO teams up with Beardo to make the perfect meal for Carol.

added.title: Plaza Film Festival
added.description: When the plaza has its own film festival, KO, Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: The gang decide to compete in the annual Thumb War competition, but a surprise forces Mao Mao to deal with the unthinkable... losing.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: He's the Sheriff
added.description: The gang struggles to get rid of the King when he joins them as their new deputy-for-a-day!

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

added.title: Small
added.description: Mao Mao's legendary, gigantic and critical father visits his son at his new job as sheriff.

added.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
added.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

added.title: Ready to Rumble
added.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

added.title: Ken 10
added.description: We're back in the future with Ben 10K, and this time he has a son, Ken. On Ken's tenth birthday, Ben gives him his very own Omnitrix. Ben must come to learn to trust Ken with the power of the Omnitrix. Along the way, Ken befriends a kid named Devlin. Devlin turns out to be Kevin 11's son and was merely using Ken so he could break his dad out of the Null Void. Ben 10K and Ken then team up to take down Kevin 11. As for Devlin, he comes to realize his dad is a jerk, and realizes the error of his ways. He's able to redeem himself, proving he's a good kid and joining forces with "Team Tennyson."

added.title: The More Things Change Part 1
added.description: Now on his own, Ben sets out to be a solo superhero, with new alien heroes at his disposal, but Grandpa Max has other plans. (Introducing Rook, Malware, Khyber, Nemetrix alien Crabdozer, new Ben aliens Feedback & Blox, Pakmar.)

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: A Jolt from the Past
added.description: Alien pests from Ben's youth come back, but now they need Ben's help. (Introducing Fistrick, & new Ben alien Gravattack.)

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Have I Got a Deal for You
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop a giant rampaging alien from destroying Bellwood while dealing with a peace-loving alien-rights activist who doesn't want it hurt. (Introducing Hokestar, Solid Plugg 1st appearance, Pax, Sunder.)

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Winning at Whining
added.description: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Changeable Terraingable
added.description: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

added.title: Chess Master Steve
added.description: Pizza Steve goes to great lengths in order to beat Mr. Gus at a game of chess.

added.title: Tiny Miracle's Tiny Miracle
added.description: Upon seeing the gang have a fun time swimming and eating ice cream, Tiny Miracle realizes he wants to be a real boy.

added.title: Uncle Greedpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in need of some extra cash, so he starts charging for his services.

added.title: Exquisite Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa has been having some truly bizarre night terrors.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa: The High School Years
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and friends go way back to when they were in high school together.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: El Onceavo Alienigena Parte 1
added.description: Con sus nuevas Omni-Mejoras, Ben intenta salvar una ciudad de un repentino alud. Pero su heroísmo dura poco, porque llega Vilgax a advertirlo de las consecuencias del misterioso alien del Omnitrix.

added.title: El Onceavo Alienigena Parte 2
added.description: Ben descubre que Vilgax se ha unido a los Weatherheads para obligarlo a entregar el Omnitrix. Ahora no solo deberá superar sus dudas, sino también aceptar sus nuevos poderes, si es que quiere derrotar a sus enemigos.

added.title: A Media
added.description: Durante un viaje al Lago de los Ozarks, Ben y Gwen discuten sobre la innecesaria celebración de "medio cumpleaños" de Ben. Pero cuando Max se entera de un sospechoso desprendimiento de rocas cercano, los primos deben dejar de lado sus diferencias si quieren rescatar a los mineros atrapados y revelar quién está detrás de la catástrofe producida por el hombre antes de que sea demasiado tarde: los hermanos Bugg.

added.title: El regreso de Xingo
added.description: Cuando Ben debe divertirse solo durante la merecida siesta de Max, se topa con un juego de Xingo y decide convertirse en OE-Shock Rock para encenderlo. Pero cuando Xingo recibe demasiada carga, salta al mundo real, y nuestro héroe debe quedar frente a frente con su personaje animado favorito.

added.title: Cazarecompensas
added.description: Mientras Gwen escucha una conferencia sobre el Ferrocarril Transcontinental, Ben se escapa en secreto a la tienda de regalos. Pero una vez que los Cazarrecompensas aparecen y acorralan a nuestro héroe, Gwen debe transmitir la información que aprendió en el tren y utilizarla para ayudar a Ben a escapar.

added.title: Consejos
added.description: Amatista ha estado ayudando a las Gemas de Pequeña Escuela Madre a encontrar trabajo, pero Steven no está seguro de su enfoque.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Monstruo en el Jardin
added.description: Craig está decidido a atrapar al monstruo que ha estado desatando un caos en el jardín del abuelo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Maldicion
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP entran en conflicto con unas brujas adolescentes deshonestas, ique les lanzan una maldición! iQué adolescentes malvadas!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Perro Decisivo
added.description: Incapaz de tomar decisiones difíciles, Craig decide poner sus decisiones en manos de un perro llamado Fred.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: #CortoCircuito
added.description: Leslie Willis, la chica mas cruel de la escuela, se convierte en una sensación de las redes sociales al subir videos malintencionados a su canal, haciendo que Wonder Woman cuestione la integridad moral de quienes viven en el Mundo del Hombre.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Saca tu Bestia
added.description: Craig quiere jugar a un popular juego de cartas, así que decide tomar prestadas las cartas antiguas y valiosas de Bernard.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: #AunqueSeaGigante
added.description: Karen Beecher siempre es molestada en la escuela. Pero cuando el centro comercial es atacado por una monstruosa super villana llamada Giganta, Karen descubre que la diminuta Bumblebee puede ser la única suficientemente pequeña para salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Sitiados
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

added.title: El Club de Exploradores
added.description: El ninja debe entrar en el Club del Explorador para obtener el segundo Pergamino de Spinjitzu Prohibido, en conflicto con el gerente del club y los miembros furiosos del club.

added.title: Perdidos en la Cloaca
added.description: Craig acepta ayudar a la Reina de las Alcantarillas a trazar el mapa de las alcantarillas, pero rápidamente se encuentra en una situación que lo supera.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: #BatallaEnElMuseo
added.description: Supergirl siempre confía en su fuerza, pero necesitará mas que músculos para impedir que la astuta Catwoman robe unas valiosas gemas del museo de ciencias.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Lucha de Pulgares
added.description: El trío decide concursar en la competencia anual de Lucha de Pulgares, pero una sorpresa obliga a Mao Mao a lidiar con algo impensado… la derrota.

added.title: #DeMalEnPeor
added.description: Habiéndose mudado a los aburridos suburbios de Metrópolis, Batgirl se emociona cuando intercepta una llamada de auxilio de Batman. Pero antes de que pueda ir a detener a un villano visitante de Ciudad Gótica, Barbara debe escabullirse de su casa y de su padre, el comisionado Gordon.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: La Venganza es Mia
added.description: Aspheera llega al Monasterio de Spinjitzu y se enfrenta a Wu, obligando a uno de los ninjas a hacer un sacrificio heroico.

added.title: Todo Por Mao Mismo
added.description: El deseo de Mao Mao de convertirse en leyenda lo lleva a querer superarse a sí mismo una y otra vez. ¿Pero cuánto es suficiente?

added.title: #ElFlechazo
added.description: Diana Prince está triunfando en todos los aspectos de la vida y como alumna de la Secundaria Metrópolis... hasta que alguien llega para confundirla totalmente.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Una Fria Despedida
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que Zane no está muerto, el Maestro Wu se prepara para ir tras él, pero Lloyd y el otro ninja toman el asunto en sus propias manos y desafían a su Maestro.

added.title: El es el Sheriff
added.description: iEl trío lucha por deshacerse del Rey cuando los acompaña como nuevo ayudante del sheriff por un día!

added.title: El Estornudo De Panda
added.description: Los osos panda tienen un estornudo muy adorable (iy violento!), y nuestro Panda no es la excepción. Cuando un video de su estornudo tierno se vuelve viral en la página Vine, Panda se convierte en una sensación ¿tierna¿, lo que hace que Nom Nom trate de ahuyentar a este nuevo contendiente a su trono.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Colosal adopta a un monstruo abandonado, pero es mejor dejar algunas cosas en estado salvaje.

added.title: El Camino
added.description: iEste episodio transcurre cuando los Osos son cachorritos! Los tres Osos, en su viaje por el desierto, se topan con un depósito gigante. Los Osos tratan de convertir este paraíso repleto de cajas en su hogar.

added.title: Pequeno
added.description: El legendario, gigantesco y crítico padre de Mao Mao visita a su hijo en su nuevo trabajo como sheriff.

added.title: Emergencia
added.description: Cuando Pardo llega a su casa con un cangrejo vivo, piensa que el cangrejo puede ser una mascota para los tres hermanos. Sin embargo, cuando el cangrejo le pellizca la oreja a Polar y no lo suelta, Panda y Pardo tienen que llevar a su hermano lastimado al hospital, ide inmediato!

added.title: Vida Ecologica
added.description: Cuando un vendedor moderno en un almacén avergüenza a los Osos por pedir bolsas de plástico, los Osos se dan cuenta de que las bolsas de tela ecológicas son su forma de lograr aceptación entre las personas progresistas del Área de la Bahía. Pero en su esfuerzo por conseguir popularidad, los Osos dejan que la cultura (y la cantidad) de bolsas de tela se apodere de sus vidas.

added.title: Charlie Y La Serpiente
added.description: Charlie (alias Pie Grande) es un tipo solitario a quien, como a los Osos, le gustaría encontrar un lugar en el mundo. En su intento por conseguirlo, Charlie organiza una fiesta, pero termina embarcándose en una aventura con el más improbable de los animales: una serpiente salvaje.

added.title: Pelea Bot
added.description: La Dra. Fox se enorgullece de presentar su nueva máquina de combate definitiva y llevarla a un ring de combate científico subterráneo. Pero Hawkodile está celoso del bot de combate de la Dra. Fox, que supuestamente da mejores golpes que él, y declara que puede vencer a cualquier cosa que el bot pueda. Para demostrar su afirmación, se viste con piezas de robot de repuesto y entra en secreto en la batalla de robots. Con Unikitty como su entrenadora de lucha, ¿podrá Hawkodile sobrevivir al torneo, demostrar que es más fuerte que una máquina y salvarse del depósito de chatarra?

added.title: Dia de Playa
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se preparan para un día divertido en la playa, pero cuando Master Frown aparece como socorrista para arruinar sus planes en la arena, Unikitty y la pandilla se embarcan en una búsqueda para encontrar el legendario lugar perfecto, lejos del dominio tiránico de Frown. Pero ¿podrán llegar allí antes de que Frown lo reclame para él o su búsqueda se convertirá en un verdadero fastidio playero?

added.title: Perrote, Probloemita
added.description: Después de un percance en el laboratorio, itodos en el castillo, excepto Puppycorn, se reducen a un tamaño diminuto! A Puppycorn le parece genial. iSus amigos son como muñecos coleccionables vivientes! Así que comienza a jugar con ellos en aventuras imaginarias. Unikitty y los demás piensan que ser miniaturas y jugar con Puppycorn es sorprendentemente divertido, pero Puppycorn tiene el hábito de romper por accidente sus juguetes, y pronto estará claro que la banda tendrá que hacer una huida audaz y diminuta de vuelta al laboratorio antes de que Puppycorn los haga trizas de tanto amor.

added.title: Magia Tragica
added.description: Cuando Richard monta un espectáculo de magia amateur, la Dra. Fox se obsesiona por descubrir cómo se hacen esos trucos que desafían la ciencia. Pero mientras se propone usar todo su intelecto para encontrar formas experimentales de hacer los trucos que vio en la fiesta del cachorro, ¿acaso arruinará accidentalmente el asombro de la magia?

added.title: Balarin Peligroso
added.description: El Unireino organizó un baile para todo el reino: un evento divertido donde todos se disfrazan y se ponen a bailar. Todo el mundo está emocionado, excepto Richard, al que le aterra dejarse llevar y sentir su ritmo interior. Unikitty sabe que Rick necesita expresarse, pero ¿pueden ella y los demás convencerlo de salir de su caparazón con algunas pequeñas mejoras de su cuerpo robótico?

added.title: La Cosa en la Pared
added.description: Cuando Axel y el equipo acusan a Galileo de robar sus posesiones, el lagarto debe cazar al verdadero culpable, una misteriosa criatura detrás del muro, para demostrar su inocencia.

added.title: La Trampa de Madcap
added.description: Madcap y Princess SugarSalt atrapan a Axel y al equipo dentro de un laberinto impulsado por Minergy que los ataca con sus mayores temores, obligándolos a trabajar juntos y escapar como una unidad.

added.title: A Domar Los Cielos Peligrosos
added.description: Con el ala del avión no tripulado de Axel roto, el equipo debe encontrar otra forma de detener a Madcap y sus secuaces mientras se lanzan a los cielos en aviones de juguete para un asalto aéreo en el parque de la ciudad.

added.title: Efectos en Cuatro Colores
added.description: Axel, Galileo y Sarge son transportados por Minergy por Madcap a las páginas del cómic favorito de Axel, cuyo héroe resulta no ser tan genial después de todo.

added.title: Sonrie y Aguanta
added.description: Cuando un dolor de muelas envía a Axel al dentista, el equipo debe luchar contra la Princesa SugarSalt, quien confunde la nueva "corona" de Axel con la realidad.

added.title: Una Leccion para Todos
added.description: Los Fantásticos le enseñan a unos chicos del vecindario a no imitar a los demás. Por ejemplo, a quienes utilizan a sus Bakugan con fines frívolos.

added.title: Heroes Locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Bromas Pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Ene-Amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 2
added.description: Dan y sus amigos ganan la Batalla Bakugan, demostrando que los Fantásticos son nuestros héroes y los mejores Peleadores Bakugan.

added.title: Un Almuerzo Inesperado
added.description: Cuando el Restaurante de Hamburguesas es amenazado por un violento Bakugan, Dan llega para salvar el día...y las hamburguesas.

added.title: El Miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 1
added.description: Dan conoce a su pareja Bakugan, Drago, por primera vez y nos enteramos del "incidente" que ocurrió en la Tierra hace doce años.

added.title: El Bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

removed.description: The Thunderkittens plug a new video game cartridge into Snarf only to learn that it didn't load a game, it loaded a whole new personality into their pal! Meet Schnorp, a kind Swedish man who loves the beauty of nature and collecting berries! Schnorp is loads of fun, but we're gonna want Snarf back, right?

removed.title: El Futuro
removed.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.

removed.description: Afirmando que es bueno de corazón, Dynamo convence a Axel y al equipo para que lo ayuden a encontrar una batería que pueda alimentar su centrífuga y liberarlo del control de Madtrap, pero Bobbie Blobby no está comprando la historia del malo.

removed.title: #SuperWho?
removed.description: Overwhelmed by the amount of Superman coverage in Metropolis, Supergirl decides to get out there and really show the city what she can do. removed.title: #LaCubetaDeBurritos
removed.description: A Babs le encanta su trabajo en el restaurante de comida rápida "La Cubeta de Burritos" , pero a su jefe, que está harto de que ella siempre llegue tarde y de su enorme dispersión, le encantaría encontrar cualquier excusa para despedirla. Pero ¿será capaz de salvar a todos y conservar su empleo justo a tiempo?
removed.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

removed.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

removed.title: Salvajessa
removed.description: Un encuentro con Salvajessa, guardiana de la naturaleza, inspira a Kelsey a dedicarse a una causa.
removed.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

removed.title: Superado
removed.description: Cuando Rufus y Reg llegan para engañar al pueblo, el sheriff Mao Mao les enseña una lección sobre la justicia.

removed.title: The News Never Sleeps!
removed.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

removed.description: Con la esperanza de reparar su fuerte, Craig consigue la ayuda de Los Veloces Diez para llevarlos hasta la legendaria pila de basura.

removed.title: Baba Yaga House
removed.description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

removed.description: Cuando el departamento del sheriff se enfrenta a un monstruo que copia todos los movimientos, tendrán que encontrar el modo de pelear sin pelear.

removed.description: The ninja rush to the NINJAGO Museum of History to recover a dangerous scroll before it falls into the hands of the Serpentine Sorceress Aspheera.

removed.description: JP dirties his last clean clothes and he must wear his Sunday best to the creek.

removed.description: iAxel y Bobbie Blobby se saltan los simulacros de preparación para desastres de Sarge, dejando suficiente espacio en las defensas del equipo para que un cuervo se precipite y arrebata a Sarge! Sintiéndose responsable, Axel lidera al equipo en una misión de búsqueda y rescate.

removed.title: The Future
removed.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

removed.description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

removed.description: When Val starts a romantic match-making service, he struggles being true to his own feelings for his secret crush.
